                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/609.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-08-02T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 2, 1911—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Knox instructs Mr. Furniss in reply to his August 1, 1 and 3 p.m., that he
                    may accord temporary refuge to President Simon in the legation if necessary to
                    save innocent human life.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
